<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1713,1992]" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,1713,1739]" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[233,417,1713,1740]" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 384" refId="ref16242" refString="Bequaert, J. (1918) A revision of the Vespidae of the Belgian Congo based on the Collection of the American Museum Congo Expedition, with a list of the Ethiopian Diplopterous Wasps. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 39 (1), 1 - 384." type="journal article" year="1918">Bequaert (1918)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maidl" authorityYear="1914" box="[541,614,1713,1739]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[541,614,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[670,774,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">maculata</emphasis>
as new varieties of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1003,1196,1714,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[1003,1196,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on specimens that he believed were conspecific with the taxa described four years before by Maidl as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maidl" authorityYear="1914" box="[1151,1330,1749,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[1151,1330,1749,1776]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maidl" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="similis" variety="maculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris similis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[354,458,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The taxa described by Bequaert are indeed color forms of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1159,1277,1786,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[1159,1277,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">S. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the ones described by Maidl clearly belong to a distinct species, more closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1903" box="[1053,1139,1821,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[1053,1139,1821,1848]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">S. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1203,1320,1822,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis box="[1203,1320,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">S. cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Bequaert therefore created two cases of homonymy, of which one was corrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpenter, J. M. &amp; Gusenleitner, J. &amp; Madl, M." box="[983,1238,1857,1883]" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" pagination="95 - 315" refId="ref16296" refString="Carpenter, J. M., Gusenleitner, J. &amp; Madl, M. (2010) A Catalogue of the Eumeninae (Hymenoptera: Vespidae) of the Ethiopian Region excluding Malagasy Subregion. Part II: Genera Delta de Saussure 1855 to Zethus Fabricius 1804 and Species Incertae Sedis. Linzer biologische Beitrage, 42 (1), 95 - 315." type="journal article" year="2010">
Carpenter 
<emphasis box="[1100,1156,1857,1883]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
with the proposition of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carpenter, Gusenleitner &amp; Madl" box="[342,656,1893,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cornuta" subSpecies="similoides">
<emphasis box="[342,656,1893,1920]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris cornuta similoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bequard" authorityYear="1918" box="[945,1267,1893,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="cornuta" variety="similis">
<emphasis box="[945,1138,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris cornuta</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1194,1267,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To correct the other case, the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selis &amp; Carpenter" authorityYear="2022" box="[397,750,1929,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cornuta" subSpecies="maculatoides">
<emphasis box="[397,750,1929,1956]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris cornuta maculatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed as replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Bequaert, 1918" authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Synagris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="cornuta" variety="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1191,1385,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">Synagris cornuta</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[151,255,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">maculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[262,436,1965,1992]" pageId="22" pageNumber="509" pagination="1 - 384" refId="ref16242" refString="Bequaert, J. (1918) A revision of the Vespidae of the Belgian Congo based on the Collection of the American Museum Congo Expedition, with a list of the Ethiopian Diplopterous Wasps. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 39 (1), 1 - 384." type="journal article" year="1918">Bequaert, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[447,489,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="509">non</emphasis>
Maidl, 1914.
</paragraph>
